  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Drain and rinse your <strong>butter beans</strong></p><p>Add the<strong> drained</strong> <strong>butter beans </strong>to a <strong>food processor</strong> and blitz until smooth</p><p>Peel and grate <strong>half </strong>your <strong>red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely slice the <strong>remaining red onion</strong> and set aside</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1695715654763-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1695715654763-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1695715654763-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1695715654763-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1695715654763-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>blended beans</strong>, <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong>, <strong>peri peri spice mix </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>and <strong>grated onion </strong>to a bowl and mix thoroughly until fully combined (clean hands is the best way!) – this is your <strong>bean mixture</strong></p><p>Divide the <strong>bean mixture</strong> into 1 flat patty per person</p><p>Line a tray with <strong>baking paper</strong>, add the <strong>peri peri butter bean patty[ies] </strong>to the tray and put in the oven for an initial 25 min until starting to crisp</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1695715659062-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1695715659062-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1695715659062-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1695715659062-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1695715659062-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut your <strong>potatoes </strong>(skins on) into chips</p><p>Add the <strong>chips</strong> to one side of a separate baking tray (or two) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-9-1695717264585-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-9-1695717264585-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-9-1695717264585-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-9-1695717264585-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-9-1695717264585-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>sweetcorn cobettes</strong> to a large piece of<strong> tin foil </strong>(or two!)</p><p>Add a small pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and scrunch the <strong>tin foil </strong>around the corn until tightly sealed and add to the other side of the baking tray[s]</p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for 25-30 min or until the chips are golden and crisp</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1695715707752-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1695715707752-x400.jpg",
